---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE, url } from '@/lib/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-4 sm:px-8">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">About</h1>

    <div class="prose-editorial mt-6">
      <p>
        Anant Sudarshan is an environmental and energy economist whose work sits
        at the intersection of economics and engineering. His research spans the
        design of environmental regulation, air pollution, climate change, energy
        efficiency, electricity access and renewable energy — much of it built on
        field experiments and administrative data from India.
      </p>
      <p>
        He is a Professor in the Department of Economics at the University of
        Warwick. Before joining Warwick in 2022 he spent eight years at the
        Energy Policy Institute at the University of Chicago (EPIC) — latterly as
        its South Asia Director — and earlier held research positions at
        Harvard's Kennedy School and MIT.
      </p>
      <p>
        He received his PhD in Management Science and Engineering from Stanford
        University, and holds undergraduate and master's degrees in mechanical
        engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology (Delhi) and Stanford
        University respectively.
      </p>
      <p>
        A recurring thread in his work is whether market-based environmental
        policy can function where enforcement is weak: with collaborators he
        designed and ran a randomized evaluation of the world's first market for
        particulate air pollution, among industrial plants in Surat. Other
        projects measure the often-hidden costs of environmental change — from
        the effect of heat on factory productivity to the surge in human
        mortality that followed the collapse of India's vultures.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a
        href={url('/cv')}
        class="rounded-md border border-[var(--color-line)] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]"
        >Curriculum vitae</a
      >
      <a
        href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}
        class="rounded-md border border-[var(--color-line)] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]"
        >Email</a
      >
      <a
        href={SITE.links.scholar}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="rounded-md border border-[var(--color-line)] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]"
        >Google Scholar</a
      >
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
